@DETROID_NTR, you do realize that Adachi Yoshinobu doesn't exist, right? A simple Google Search takes me to fucking Ghost of Tsushima. Now, don't get me wrong, I fucking love that game (god, I just hate that last boss) but can you not mix games with legitimate history? The Adachi Clan DOES INDEED exist; they were players during the Genpei War (so around the time Tomoe Gozen, Kiichi Hogen, and Minamoto no Yoshitsune were active in). None of their members carry the name of Yoshinobu. The first head of the clan is named Morinaga, the second head is named Kagemori, the third head is named Yoshikage, the fourth head is named Yasumori, the fifth head is named Munekage, the sixth head is named Tokiaki, and the seventh and last head is named Takakage. No notable clan member has ever had the name of Yoshinobu and it is Adachi Morinaga and Adachi Kagemori who are "well-known"; the rest of the family are pretty much ghosts as far as my research took me.
